article.headline: Belmont 92, Florida Gulf Coast 74
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- Andy Wicke scored 17 points, making five 3-pointers, to lead five Belmont players in double figures in a 92-74 victory over Florida Gulf Coast on Saturday. Jon House and Matthew Dotson also scored 17 points apiece, while Alex Renfroe added 15 and Shane Dansby chipped in 10 for the Bruins (13-7, 9-2 Atlantic Sun Conference), who won their third straight game. Belmont hit 11 of 18 3-pointers in the first half to lead 48-30 at halftime, pulling ahead by as many as 24 in the second half. Belmont made 33 of 56 shots from the field (58.9 percent) -- 17 of 28 after halftime (60.7 percent). The Bruins made 15 of 28 3-pointers for the game. Florida Gulf Coast (9-15, 5-8), which lost its third straight, was 25-for-54 from the field (46.3 percent). Reggie Chambers led the Eagles with 19 points and six assists, while Derrick O'Neil added 15 points.
